name: Zenith Star Maker
description:
Make a generative abstract star. Use the following keys to configure your star.

Tip: You may have to click the star before the keys work.
Tip 2: Shift+key inverts the key function

Q = Changes the angle of the triangles in the star
W = Adds spokes to the star
E = Increases star size
R = Decreases star opacity
A = Increases size of background stars
S = Increases space between background stars
D = Increases the inner radius of background stars
F = Increases background stars per ring
G = Decreases background star opacity
H = Increases background stars per ring
Z = Increases hue of colors
X = Increases saturation of colors
C = Increases light of colors
V = Increases color variability
